Name: Cogs
Description: Common material that contains important compounds.
WorldDesc: Standard cog widely used in industrial production during the Golden Age. It became the key to Construct development when the Ta-193 copolymer that it contains was found to have extremely high biological affinity.

Name: Black Card
Description: Special card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Issued to squads as funding and managed by the Commandant.

Name: Black Card
Description: Special card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Issued to squads as funding and managed by the Commandant.

Name: Serum
Description: Required for the Commandant to enter battle.
WorldDesc: Protects the human body from the Punishing for a certain amount of time, and supplied to Babylonia's frontline squads reguarly.

Name: Rainbow Card
Description: Premium card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Premium card that can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Managed by the Commandant.

Name: Bullion
WorldDesc: Placeholder

Name: Squad EXP
Description: Represents a squad's performance records. Accumulate EXP to increase squad rating.

Name: Rainbow Card
Description: Premium card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Premium card that can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Managed by the Commandant.

Name: Rainbow Card
Description: Premium card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Premium card that can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Managed by the Commandant.

Name: Friendship Point
Description: Level of friendship with a contact.

Name: Skill Point
Description: Data program that increases members' understanding of skills and raises their skill levels.
WorldDesc: Chip containing skill data. Helps members improve their skills.

Name: Daily Activity
Description: Activity gained from completing Daily Missions. Resets at 07:00 AM UTC daily.

Name: Weekly Activity
Description: Activity gained from completing Daily Missions. Resets at 07:00 AM UTC on Monday.

Name: Particle
Description: Generated by the Dormitory power plant.

Name: Material
WorldDesc: Materials obtained from recycling. Can be remade into various useful items.

Name: Scavenger MK-II
WorldDesc: Robot developed by Babylonia. Able to survive exposure to the Punishing for brief periods of time, it can help find useful materials on the battlefield.

Name: Bounty EXP
WorldDesc: Special reward that increases Bounty level. Complete different missions to get different bonuses. "Aim for the top." —Anonymous Construct

Name: Test item
WorldDesc: Test item

Name: Current
Description: Progress earned from completing Novice Missions.
WorldDesc: Thank you, Commandant. - Gray Raven

Name: Fragment Shard
WorldDesc: Different combinations of the same shards may lead to different results. - Asimov

Name: Scavenger MK-II
WorldDesc: Robot developed by Babylonia. Able to survive exposure to the Punishing for brief periods of time, it can help find useful materials on the battlefield.

Name: War Zone Influence
Description: Currency for War Zone. Can be used in the War Shop.
WorldDesc: Conflicts of various kinds can arise in the War Zone. Those who have influence are often in a position to determine the final outcome of these Event.

Name: 4★ Weapon Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 4★ weapon. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 5★ Weapon Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 5★ weapon. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 6★ Weapon Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 6★ weapon. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 4★ Memory Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 4★ Memory Chip. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 5★ Memory Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 5★ Memory Chip. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: 6★ Memory Shard
WorldDesc: Parts obtained from recycling a 6★ Memory Chip. Can be used to manufacture other weapons of the same grade, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: Dorm Coin
Description: Used for Dormitory Research and other actions.
WorldDesc: Shiny coins that can be spent to perform research and other Dormitory-related actions.

Name: Decor Coin
Description: Parts obtained from recycling Decor. Can be reassembled into other Decor.
WorldDesc: Recycle existing Decor to obtain materials to produce new Decor, maximizing the use of resources.

Name: Coating Blueprint
WorldDesc: Design blueprint that records Coating schematics in detail, used to produce new Coatings.

Name: Coating Sketch
Description: Can be exchanged for Coating Blueprints.
WorldDesc: Rough sketch of a Coating design. Conveys the designer's concept, but not quite detailed enough to put into production.

Name: A-Class Inver Material
WorldDesc: Material obtained from recycling Inver-Shards. Highly valuable and can be exchanged for various supplies at Babylonia.

Name: S-Class Inver Material
WorldDesc: Material obtained from recycling Inver-Shards. Extremely valuable and can be exchanged for various supplies at Babylonia.

Name: Residence Permit
Description: Used to unlock a new Dormitory.
WorldDesc: Permit to build new Dormitory facilities at the HQ.

Name: Proof of Honor
Description: Upvote others members of the United Command Bureau to increase their Popularity.
WorldDesc: A special proof of popularity.

Name: Command Bureau Contribution
Description: Indicates the contribution you have made to the Command Bureau. Forms the basis for Command Bureau Contribution Rankings.
WorldDesc: Can be gained by participating in Command Bureau challenges

Name: United Achievement Points
Description: Rewarded to participants in Command Bureau challenges. Can be exchanged for various resources in Point Shop.
WorldDesc: Tokens rewarded to participants in Command Bureau events

Name: Command Bureau EXP
Description: You can level up the Command Bureau after gaining enough Command Bureau EXP.
WorldDesc: You can accumulate EXP for your Command Bureau by participating in Command Bureau challenges.

Name: Return Progress
Description: The progress of returning player missions. Will be reset once the returning period ends.

Name: Type II Vote
Description: Use this item to give likes to your favorite comments in Eden II forum.
WorldDesc: Each vote has a unique identification code. Enter the code in Eden II to get likes. The votes will be reset to zero at the end of every event.

Name: Progress
Description: The progress of completion for Eden II Event targets.
WorldDesc: Thank you, Commandant. - Gray Raven

Name: Pioneer Medal
Description: The proof of participation in the pioneer test. Can be exchanged for Black Cards in the live server. Stay tuned to further announcements for more detail.

Name: Weapon Coating Blueprint
Description: Can be exchanged for Weapon Coatings.
WorldDesc: Design blueprint that records Weapon Coating schematics in detail, used to produce new Weapon Coatings.

Name: Beacon Amplifier Points
Description: Gained by leveling up the Command Bureau. Allow you to level up Beacon Amplifier.
WorldDesc: An indicator of the team effort put into developing the Command Bureau.

Name: Special Support Token
Description: Can be exchanged for items in Resource Shop
WorldDesc: A silver spinning top crafted from special materials. Bears a QR code that projects the words "Support Force" upon being scanned. Can be exchanged in Resource Shop for supplies that Babylonia has specially requisitioned for high-performing squads.

Name: S-Rank Uniframe Material
Description: Obtained by deconstructing the corresponding Inver-Shard.
WorldDesc: The material obtained by deconstructing extra Inver-Shards has a higher recycle value and can be used to exchange any material in Babylonia.

Name: Scene Blueprint
Description: Can be exchanged for main scenes.
WorldDesc: Design blueprint that records various sections of the scene in detail, used to produce new scenes.

Name: Action Points
WorldDesc: Autopoiesis Maze Action Points

Name: Aberrant Cube
Description: Can purchase add-on units in Autopoiesis Maze
WorldDesc: The smaller version of a common material for industrial production. Can quickly produce add-ons and tools, among other things, based on the blueprint provided. Caveat: non-standard materials like this are worthless outside Autopoiesis Maze.

Name: Add-On Unit
Description: Gain a random add-on unit to power up members in Autopoiesis Maze.
WorldDesc: An integrator of certain add-on efficacy. Only works in Autopoiesis Maze.

Name: Command Bureau Name Change Card
Description: It can change the name of your Command Bureau. Note that only the Commandant with the highest authority level can use it.

Name: War Zone Merit
Description: Merits are earned based on the Commandant's War Zone rank. To advance from Hero Squad to Legendary Squad, 100 Merit points are required.
WorldDesc: Commandants who have made outstanding contributions in War Zone are always favored in Babylonia. They are awarded appropriately by the military.

Name: Battle Data
Description: Chestlefield's tokens. Used for purchasing Tactic Cards in Tactic Reserve.
WorldDesc: A very scientific small terminal that can capture real-time combat data and analyze it.

Name: Kinetic Potion
WorldDesc: An uneventful can filled with a strangely smelling liquid. According to its maker, the graffiti painted on the surface of the can "is a security mark."

Name: Core Module
WorldDesc: An exquisite mechanical heart. The built-in new kinetic energy module can convert the high concentration kinetic energy liquid stored in the device into energy for continuous operation of the mechanoid, greatly improving its performance.

Name: Minor Core Module
Description: Micawberism Cloisters minor rank up items
WorldDesc: A less exquisite but still practical mechanic heart is the best choice for the budget and the pursuit of cost-effectiveness!

Name: Trap Doll
Description: The stage skip item of Infiniteness Chapter can be used to skip stages, and be recycled by challenging the skipped stages.
WorldDesc: A doll made by Nanami. No one knows what she did to it to make the trap doll briefly attract the attention of other corrupteds... and take advantage of this interval, allows Nanami to advance to the next layer quickly!

Name: Intel Value
Description: Obtain from completing Rating Mission. Accumulate to increase Rating Level.
WorldDesc: Complete the Rating Missions to earn Intel Value, an important measure of your Rating Level. Sometimes a trivial detail may determine the outcome of a battle. Make good use of everything you have got.

Name: A-Rank Structure Material
WorldDesc: The material obtained by deconstructing extra CUBs has higher recycle value and can be used to exchange any material in Babylonia

Name: S-Rank Structure Material
WorldDesc: The material obtained by deconstructing extra CUBs has higher recycle value and can be used to exchange any material in Babylonia

Name: Signal Diffuser
Description: A Circuit Connect item that can unlock skills in the shop. Can be obtained through completing missions.
WorldDesc: A part that can be used to expand signal band capacity and range of effect. Its ease of use, compatibility, and stability have made it a widely used item in various scenes. It's an indispensable item for both internal and external operations.

Name: Signal Anchor
Description: A Circuit Connect item that can unlock characters in the shop. Can be obtained through completing missions.
WorldDesc: A microelectronic unit once used to locate signals. As one of the indispensable parts in the electronic industry during the Golden Age, it was mass-produced and used in various fields. Although its basic technology and form have changed countless times, the item still enjoys a stable position.

Name: Unipower Module
Description: Use it to exchange for items in the Operation Uniframe Shop
WorldDesc: Awarded to participants of Operation Uniframe

Name: Bonus Move
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Add 1 Step. 9 rounds cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Red
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Red Orbs by 50% for 1 round. 5 rounds cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Blue
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Blue Orbs by 50% for 1 round. 5 rounds cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Yellow
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Yellow Orbs by 50% for 1 round. 5 rounds cooldown.

Name: Enhanced Basic Attack
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Increases the Damage Points of Basic Attack Orbs by 50% for 1 round. 5 rounds cooldown.

Name: Clear One Row
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Remove one row. 8 rounds cooldown.

Name: Clear One Column
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Remove one column. 8 rounds cooldown.

Name: Clear Same Color
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Remove all orbs of the same color. 12 rounds cooldown.

Name: Change Orb
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Changes the color of orbs. 12 rounds cooldown.

Name: Swap Orb
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock skills during the event.
WorldDesc: Swap two orbs. 5 rounds cooldown.

Name: Nanami: Storm
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock a character during the event.
WorldDesc: Unlocks character "Nanami: Storm"

Name: Lee: Palefire
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock a character during the event.
WorldDesc: Unlocks character "Lee: Palefire"

Name: Watanabe: Nightblade
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock a character during the event.
WorldDesc: Unlocks character "Watanabe: Nightblade"

Name: Lucia: Plume
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock a character during the event.
WorldDesc: Unlocks character "Lucia: Plume"

Name: Vera: Garnet
Description: Once purchased, this Circuit Connect item can unlock a character during the event.
WorldDesc: Unlocks character "Vera: Garnet"

Name: Letter of Invitation
Description: Use to choose a character in Accumulated Top-up Choice Shop - Character Exchange.
WorldDesc: Invite a character of your choice. <color=#FF0000FF>Characters released in subsequent versions will gradually enter the Accumulated Top-up Choice Shop.</color>

Name: Weapon Coupon
Description: Use to choose a weapon in Accumulated Top-up Choice Shop - Weapon Exchange.
WorldDesc: Weapons can significantly influence the outcome of a battle. <color=#FF0000FF>Weapons released in subsequent versions will gradually enter the Accumulated Top-up Choice Shop.</color>

Name: CUB Coupon
Description: Use to choose a CUB in Accumulated Top-up Choice Shop - CUB Exchange.
WorldDesc: Aim to be a CUB master! Let's go! <color=#FF0000FF>CUBs released in subsequent versions will gradually enter the Accumulated Top-up Choice Shop.</color>

Name: Rainbow Card
Description: Premium card that can be exchanged for various materials.
WorldDesc: Premium card that can be exchanged for resources in Humanity Front territory. Managed by the Commandant.

Name: Strange Mark
WorldDesc: Its nature is completely unknown.

Name: Popular Gift
Description: Can be gifted to another Commandant in the Command Bureau. The recipient gains 10 Popularity while the giver receives 1 United Achievement Point.
WorldDesc: Can be gained by playing the combat supply stage AE-5

Name: Trade Voucher
Description: Can be exchanged for items in Shop - Voucher Exchange
WorldDesc: A voucher that records resource transactions, which will be submitted for approval.

Name: Dispatch Certificate
Description: Can be exchanged for items in Dormitory Shop [Dispatch Shop].
WorldDesc: Issued by Babylonia to individuals who have completed the commissions. Can be used to apply for extra supplies. Some Constructs also keep it as a medal.

Name: Supply Card
Description: Awarded to those who have completed the special return missions
WorldDesc: This coupon is issued to commandants in the special return event and allows them to redeem supplies of their choice. Accumulate to increase the Special Return Battle Pass level.

Name: Creation Operator
Description: Collect a number of them to claim rewards in Clash Reflection.
WorldDesc: Awarded to those who have cleared the Clash Reflection challenges. Rewards can be claimed in Clash Reflection based on the number of operators collected. Removed at the end of every Clash Reflection event.

Name: Phantom Pain Scar
Description: Obtained from Phantom Pain Cage. Can be exchanged for useful items
WorldDesc: Parts retrieved from powerful Corrupted, key to unlocking the secrets of the Punishing Virus. Can be exchanged for supplies.

Name: HQ Shard
Description: Made from scrap metal. Can be exchanged for items with the Support Force.

Name: Shark-speare Figurine
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Park Parade."
WorldDesc: A 1:15 limited-edition Shark-speare figurine gained after "playing" with Shark-speare, with quality varying depending on the level. All it ever does is play the same nursery rhyme over and over: "Let's play and be friends! Shark-speare loves eating the Gingerbread Man!"

Name: Shark-speare Figurine
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Park Parade." (Collectible upgraded to blue)
WorldDesc: A 1:15 limited-edition Shark-speare figurine gained after "playing" with Shark-speare, with quality varying depending on the level. All it ever does is play the same nursery rhyme over and over: "Let's play and be friends! Shark-speare loves eating the Gingerbread Man!"

Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Park Parade." (Collectible upgraded to purple)
WorldDesc: A 1:15 limited-edition Shark-speare figurine gained after "playing" with Shark-speare, with quality varying depending on the level. All it ever does is play the same nursery rhyme over and over: "Let's play and be friends! Shark-speare loves eating the Gingerbread Man!"

Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Park Parade." (Collectible upgraded to orange)
WorldDesc: A 1:15 limited-edition Shark-speare figurine gained after "playing" with Shark-speare, with quality varying depending on the level. All it ever does is play the same nursery rhyme over and over: "Let's play and be friends! Shark-speare loves eating the Gingerbread Man!"

Name: Amberia Figure
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Karma Tidal."
WorldDesc: The souvenir received after defeating Amberia. Displays different colors as it levels up. Let all the guilt and nightmares end here—

Name: Amberia Figure
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Karma Tidal." (Collectible upgraded to blue)
WorldDesc: The souvenir received after defeating Amberia. Displays different colors as it levels up. Let all the guilt and nightmares end here—

Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Karma Tidal." (Collectible upgraded to orange)
WorldDesc: The souvenir received after defeating Amberia. Displays different colors as it levels up. Let all the guilt and nightmares end here—

Name: Luna's Data Sample
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Kowloong Theater."
WorldDesc: The combat illusion collected by Babylonia. Displays different colors as it levels up. Available after simulating the battle against Luna. Her formidable power can be felt even from the sample.

Name: Luna's Data Sample
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Kowloong Theater." (Collectible upgraded to blue)
WorldDesc: The combat illusion collected by Babylonia. Displays different colors as it levels up. Available after simulating the battle against Luna. Her formidable power can be felt even from the sample.

Name: Lost Fragment
Description: The material earned from clearing "Theater Ruins" missions. Can be converted into puzzle shards in the "Fragment Reunited" event.
WorldDesc: These fragments contain the image of the past. After processing, the complete data will be presented to "her."

Name: Permission Code
Description: The material earned from clearing "Hidden Current" missions. Can be converted into puzzle shards in the "Virtual Space" event.
WorldDesc: This piece of classified Babylonian information is only available to those with sufficient authority level.

Name: Unknown Rubbings
Description: The item obtained from the Event Mission can be converted into Puzzle Shards in the Mission of "Lost Inscription".
WorldDesc: After finishing the rubbings, it seems that you still need to solve the puzzle to reveal the answer, but at least you don't have to rely on luck.

Name: Memory on Stage
Description: The item obtained from the Event Mission can be converted into Puzzle Shards in the Mission of "Ballad of the Old Days".
WorldDesc: Just a fragment of memory. Is it a story that has already took place or just a possibility?

Name: Key of Truth
Description: The item obtained from the Event Mission can be converted into Puzzle Shards in the Mission of "Veiled Rift".
WorldDesc: A silver key with mysterious pattern. The key is the tool to solve the puzzle. The one with the silver key, which secret of the world did you reveal?

Name: Origami Windmill
Description: The item obtained from the Event Mission can be converted into Puzzle Shards in the Mission of "Futurismo".
WorldDesc: A simple toy made of easy-to-get materials. It has become a hit soon after a pink-haired Construct from Babylonia taught a kid in a Conservation Area how to make it.

Name: Luna's Data Sample
Description: A souvenir received after clearing "Kowloong Theater." (Collectible upgraded to purple)
WorldDesc: The combat illusion collected by Babylonia. Displays different colors as it levels up. Available after simulating the battle against Luna. Her formidable power can be felt even from the sample.

Name: Christmas Voucher
Description: Use it to exchange Christmas Gifts with Constructs.
WorldDesc: Issued by Babylonia, this can be exchanged for many great things.

Name: Starry Hairclip
Description: With the stars on my hair, I wish you are here.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Sophia that can be put on the top of the Christmas tree.

Name: Snowball Bomb
Description: For decoration only. It won't explode, probably.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Karenina that can be put on the top of the Christmas tree.

Name: Ice-cream Voucher
Description: Ice-cream is a very precious thing nowadays!
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Camu that can be put on the top of the Christmas tree.

Name: Golden Retriever
Description: A pendant inspired by a popular pet.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Vera that can be put on the top of the Christmas tree.

Name: Red Packet
Description: Whether you are giving it out or getting it from others, a red packet is always the most practical gift.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Changyu that can be put on the top of the Christmas tree.

Name: Christmas Froggie
Description: A limited edition Froggie plushie that is sold on Christmas only. Very adorable.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Lucia that can be put on the trunk of the Christmas tree.

Name: Plush Sheep
Description: The production of this white and soft sheep plushie was recently restored.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Liv that can be put on the trunk of the Christmas tree.

Name: Sudoku Hell
Description: A collection of extremely difficult sudoku puzzles.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Lee that can be put on the trunk of the Christmas tree.

Name: Legends of the Wild
Description: "Legends of the Wild" is one of the most popular legendary games during the Golden Age.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Kamui that can be put on the trunk of the Christmas tree.

Name: Portable Sewing Kit
Description: A very handy kit for sewing.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Chrome that can be put on the trunk of the Christmas tree.

Name: Hometown Snowman
Description: An artificial snowman that reminds people of the snowy nights in their hometown.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Bianca that can be put at the bottom of the Christmas tree.

Name: Dragon Revelation
Description: Never give up, no matter how dire the situation is. This applies to both games and real life.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Rosetta that can be put at the bottom of the Christmas tree.

Name: Art Collection
Description: Records all the renowned artworks that were passed on from the Golden Age.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Ayla that can be put at the bottom of the Christmas tree.

Name: Old Guitar
Description: A somewhat dated guitar that can still be played.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Watanabe that can be put at the bottom of the Christmas tree.

Name: Biting Shark
Description: This trick toy was reproduced with a lot more random built-in games.
WorldDesc: A Christmas Gift from Nanami that can be put at the bottom of the Christmas tree.

Name: Mini Lantern
Description: Use it to purchase prototype parts in "Ring in the New Year" shop.
WorldDesc: A small lantern with the size of a hand. There are plenty of them everywhere. Once dismantled, they can be used as research materials.

Name: Message Card
Description: Use it to reveal the characters in [Rhyming Couplets].
WorldDesc: A Kuroro-shaped card with some blurry message on it.

Name: Venus Rose
Description: Collect this item to complete missions and receive [Rosa Tryst] event rewards.
WorldDesc: This hot-stamped rose may look gleaming gold, but it is actually made of plastic. You won't burn your hands!

Name: Venus Coupon
Description: Special coupons issued in the [Rosa Tryst] event. Allow you to play games in Venus Splash Park together with Constructs.
WorldDesc: Issued for a special day, these coupons can be used in all purchases in the park on this particular day only.

Name: Antique Mirror
Description: Use it to challenge opponents in [Fist of the Overlord!]
WorldDesc: This mirror has the power to remove all illusions. You need it to see through the opponent's action.

Name: Portable Detector
Description: Can be used to flip cards in [Shadow Diver].
WorldDesc: With this necessary detector for underwater exploration operations, you can no longer lost direction in the deep sea.

Name: Sword Command
Description: Used to play the game in [Joker in the Barrel].
WorldDesc: A sword mark appears on the strange present box with every tap. The box will go boom if the sword pierces a clown mark, similar to the game "Pop-up Pirate".

Name: Signal Point
Description: Use it to swap the position of portraits in [Signal Voice].
WorldDesc: BPN-08, humanity needs you.

Name: Race Token
Description: Use it to swap the position of portraits in [Signal Voice].
WorldDesc: BPN-08, humanity needs you.

Name: Enameled Plum Blossom
Description: Can be exchanged for points in [Springtime Tavern].
WorldDesc: An enameled flower accessory that is created by Pulao with Akdilek's support. It's said that you can exchange it for a surprising gift in Pulao's shop if you use it properly.

Name: New Year Token
Description: Use it to purchase Lottery Tickets in [New Year Lottery].
WorldDesc: New Year's Day marks the beginning of a new year. On this special day, Babylonia has launched these tokens that can be used to exchange for Lottery Tickets.

Name: Fate Token
Description: Use it to unlock [Farewell Memento] stages.
WorldDesc: It looks like a game machine token, but there are intricate patterns on it. Could they be some kind of message?

Name: Crystal-Heart Plush
Description: Use it to unlock [A Covenant of Glass] stages.
WorldDesc: That red vitrum is what it wants to give you.

Name: Moon Dust
Description: Can be used to flip cards in [Dark Eclipse].
WorldDesc: Humans have many imaginations about what's on the dark side of the moon. And that is exactly where the grayish-white dust came from.

Name: Crumpled Paper
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Voiceless Self].
WorldDesc: "Garbage" rolled up from torn pieces of paper. It was once a precious treasure for a certain child.

Name: Klein Bottle
Description: Can be used to flip cards in [Topological Manifold].
WorldDesc: A substance that exists only in imagination. Without boundaries in the conventional sense, it possesses a structure that is inexpressible and incomprehensible to humans in the current dimension. The object reconstructed here is merely a crude replica.

Name: Energy Cube
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Dark Winter Origin].
WorldDesc: Is it even possible to constrain electricity within the container [Shackle]?

Name: Tea Tin
Description: Can be exchanged for points in [Homeward Season].
WorldDesc: For many in Kowloong, tea is an indispensable part of life, a hard currency when bartering becomes necessary.

Name: Fairy Tale Page
Description: Use it to unlock [Ever After] stages.
WorldDesc: Our invincible yet adorable hero bravely and politely defeated the challengers, crushed the evil bad guys and brought back unexpected treasures... What? This page is not supposed to write about this ending? No worries, I will just discard it.

Name: Mango Hardtacks
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Explosive Celebration].
WorldDesc: This hardtack has a subtle mango flavor. It is so hard that even Constructs cannot easily chew it apart. Noctis often carries this biscuit in his pocket—it can at least buy him some time when he is unfortunately haunted by No. 21.

Name: Fair Judgment
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Reversed Order].
WorldDesc: Engraved with a scale, this copper coin is used as a token in a game designed by Dulcinea. Justice never arrives late here.

Name: Weeping Scale
Description: Use it to swap the position of portraits in [Elegy of Despair].
WorldDesc: Formed from tears, this transparent scale has ripples that sway gently with each touch, as if it is singing a distant elegy.

Name: Dodecahedron Dice
Description: Can be used to unlock puzzle pieces in [Monochrome Corridor].
WorldDesc: Dice used as key items in a certain game.

Name: Honor Medal
Description: Can be used to flip cards in [Lightbearer's Voyage].
WorldDesc: To commemorate peace and glory.

Name: Heavenly Tile
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Headstone].
WorldDesc: "In the ninth moon of the Emperor's reign, the star deviates from its ordained course, casting an unsettling omen. Cloaked in somber greys and sickly greens, its radiance undulates, foretelling imminent peril."

Name: Enter Key
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Code: Blocks].
WorldDesc: An antique from the Golden Age. One of Teddy's favorite collectibles.

Name: Snow Orchid
Description: Can be used to unlock puzzle pieces in [Silhouette of the Past].
WorldDesc: Who knows if orchids as white as snow can still be found in this broken world?

Name: Songs of Yesteryears
Description: Use it to swap the position of cards in [Abyss Tracker].
WorldDesc: Echoes from the past still resonate from underground. What message are the intermittent signals trying to convey to the fortunate one who captures them?

Name: Coupling Set
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Coupling Match].
WorldDesc: Over time, these high-dependency integrated modules have been gradually decoupled and removed during systemic optimizations and iterations.

Name: Sleepless Star
Description: Can be used to start a game in [It's Bedtime!].
WorldDesc: Originally designed for astronauts in outer space, this helmet is now sealed with deep asleep dreams.

Name: Dream's Amber
Description: Can be used to flip cards in [Snooze Button].
WorldDesc: The amber that holds infinite time.

Name: Deduction Data
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Broken Page].
WorldDesc: Incomplete Deduction Data from the future. Real, but not reliable.

Name: Misono Badge
Description: Can be used to unlock puzzle pieces in [Chilling Omen].
WorldDesc: Misono Academy badge, adorned with hydrangea petals that symbolizes its past glory and nobility.

Name: Star Cookie
Description: Use it to swap the position of cards in [Glittering Wish].
WorldDesc: Stars can talk too, you know? One, two... Haha, can you hear what they're whispering?

Name: Illusion
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Light in Indigo Waves].
WorldDesc: The ocean foam tumbles with the tide, echoing the final whispers of the dead.

Name: Darkwick I
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Dusk's Shade].
WorldDesc: Destiny woven into a wick, burning the night, illuminating the dawn.

Name: Darkwick II
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Dusk's Shade].
WorldDesc: Destiny woven into a wick, burning the night, illuminating the dawn.

Name: Darkwick III
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Dusk's Shade].
WorldDesc: Destiny woven into a wick, burning the night, illuminating the dawn.

Name: Darkwick IV
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Dusk's Shade].
WorldDesc: Destiny woven into a wick, burning the night, illuminating the dawn.

Name: Darkwick V
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Dusk's Shade].
WorldDesc: Destiny woven into a wick, burning the night, illuminating the dawn.

Name: Sand Bishop
Description: Can be used to unlock [King's Gambit] stages.
WorldDesc: Collector's edition poker with marble patterns. The decoration on it has witnessed the undefeated legend in the world of deception.

Name: Timeless Longing
Description: Can be used for recollections in [Chrono Echoes]
WorldDesc: These boxed CDs, now relics of a bygone era, may seem obsolete. But she cherishes them as her chosen medium for preserving her works. In them, she says, one can feel the gentle warmth of passing time.

Name: Poker Guessing Preview Stage
Description: Can be used to unlock [King's Gambit] stages.
WorldDesc: Collector's edition poker with marble patterns. The decoration on it has witnessed the undefeated legend in the world of deception.

Name: Abnormal Sample UNK-9
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Intertwined Fate].
WorldDesc: An anomalous Punishing sample that once caused a minor Hetero disaster. Fortunately, it was recovered by an F.O.S. student. The subsequent analysis of this sample successfully contained the spread of the disaster.

Name: Red Orb
Description: Can be used to unlock [Phantoms in the Mirror] stages.
WorldDesc: Crystallized demon's blood.

Name: Tidal Tear I
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Light in Indigo Waves].
WorldDesc: The tear of a Hetero-Creature<//HER>. Her life is etched in the dying light... bustling, beautiful, and hastily lived.

Name: Tidal Tear II
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Light in Indigo Waves].
WorldDesc: The tear of a Hetero-Creature<//HER>. Her life is etched in the dying light... bustling, beautiful, and hastily lived.

Name: Tidal Tear III
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Light in Indigo Waves].
WorldDesc: The tear of a Hetero-Creature<//HER>. Her life is etched in the dying light... bustling, beautiful, and hastily lived.

Name: Tidal Tear IV
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Light in Indigo Waves].
WorldDesc: The tear of a Hetero-Creature<//HER>. Her life is etched in the dying light... bustling, beautiful, and hastily lived.

Name: Tidal Tear V
Description: Can be used to unlock story CGs in [Light in Indigo Waves].
WorldDesc: The tear of a Hetero-Creature<//HER>. Her life is etched in the dying light... bustling, beautiful, and hastily lived.

Name: Adhesive Bandage
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Ding Dong Hammer].
WorldDesc: A must-have at home and during travels. When applied, it can quickly reduce swelling.

Name: Battleforged Module
Description: Use it to swap the position of cards in [Piercing the Heavens].
WorldDesc: Condense your thirst for victory within every strike.

Name: Dreamcatcher
Description: Can be used to start a game in [Dreams Weaved].
WorldDesc: A woven net said to catch dreams. Wrap it with spider silk and it's said to trap nightmares... but is that really true?

Name: 黑金熊卡
Description: 可在【虚像妄念】玩法中用于开启游戏。
WorldDesc: 散落在城市各处的神奇卡片，传说只要举起黑金熊卡对着天空喊出“伟大之熊”，就会有神秘人出现实现一个愿望。

Name: Return Invitation
Description: Use it to draw rewards in [Returning to Battle] - [Returning Supplies].
WorldDesc: Nice to see you again, Commandant.

Name: Merit Thank-You Note
Description: Use it to draw rewards in [Comrades Reunited] - [Frontline Supplies].
WorldDesc: Thank you for your hard work, Commandant! You're definitely a role model that inspires us to keep fighting for the goal of reclaiming Earth!

Name: Mini Frog Pendant
WorldDesc: A handmade pendant by Lucia. It might look crude but contains Lucia's best wishes to the recipient.

Name: Sweet Fruit Pie
WorldDesc: A fruit pie Liv made by Liv. Although it uses synthetic fruits, its sweetness can definitely make you fall in love with it.

Name: Sidekick
WorldDesc: A small assistant robot Lee made with redundant parts. It cannot fight but can help its owner with everyday paperwork.

Name: Meritorious Points
Description: Obtain from completing Manual Phase Mission. Accumulate to increase Meritorious Level.
WorldDesc: Meritorious Points are the standard for evaluating Commandant's training progress.

Name: Display Pose - Nightblade
WorldDesc: Obtain by gaining 10★ from the challenge stages in Arcade Anima - Nightblade's Heart-Lock Trial.

Name: Display Pose - Crimson Abyss
WorldDesc: Obtain by gaining 10★ from the challenge stages in Arcade Anima - Crimson Abyss' Heart-Lock Trial.

WorldDesc: Obtain by gaining 10★ from the challenge stages in Arcade Anima - Garnet's Heart-Lock Trial.

Name: Raven Feather
Description: An item Lucia sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: The feather of an unknown raven is placed within the pages of a journal gifted to you. The girl who has finished her last remarks of the day looks up, her hand reaching out for the flying bird in the sky unconsciously. She hopes that she can fly across the world with those she cares about like a real raven.

Name: Spare Key For Motorbike
Description: An item Alpha sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: A well-kept, vintage-looking spare key for a motorbike. You can tell how much its original owner treasured it. The key seems to be a silent invitation, one in which she will respect your wish and wait for you to set out together.

Name: Palm Pistol
Description: An item Lee sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: An intricately designed palm pistol gifted by Lee. Modified from the discarded core of his old frame, the palm-sized revolver comes with a surprisingly long range and high firepower—it seems to be a gift that has been prepared in advance. Now, Lee finally has a chance to give it to you. His warm, metal heart will keep pounding in your hand.

Name: Invitation And Keys
Description: An item Chrome sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: An invitation to a dinner banquet and a set of keys for the old Smith estate. The rectangular key card can open the side door to the garden; The key card in the shape of Strike Hawk's logo can open the front door to the reception; And the chip inside the rook can open the door to Chrome's bedroom. You are free to stay wherever you want and use whichever key you want without worry—a sign of Chrome's absolute trust in you.

Name: Painting Of The Stars
Description: An item Noan sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: A notebook you gave Noan in the past. As if to prove his determination, he has filled the book with black-and-white sketches. Apart from the sunflower he mentioned, you also find an empty corner of the library, a glass coated in condensation, and more daily snippets among the sketches. The starry sky he once abandoned is now covered in colors, resting quietly on the last page of the notebook.

Name: Photo Attachment_0810
Description: An item Liv sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: A photo of Liv's lounge taken by a house assistant-bot. The modest, healthy queen of the night on her desk has yet to bloom. A piece of sticky note is attached to the most eye-catching area. On the note is a list of grocery items, the snacks she wanted to make, the food you love, Clothes and daily supplies you needed... Everything except for things she needed. It seems like she sent you the photo by mistake when she was making preparations.

Name: Pulao's Candy
Description: An item Pulao sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: A candy figure Pulao made following a traditional recipe long lost. Apparently, the sugar syrup used to make the candy was infused with different herbs and Chinese medicine, giving it energy-recovering properties and all sorts of health benefits. Pulao was going to sell the candy, but she might have been too heavyhanded with the ingredients, and the sugar would not melt no matter what... Still, that means it can be in your possession forever and ever.

Name: Bloom Of An Eon
Description: An item Selena sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: A gemstone picked up by a girl in her endless journey. A blooming flower is preserved inside the blue ember, frozen in time across eons, never withering.

Name: Chac-Chac
Description: An item Sophia sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: A pair of Akdilek instruments gifted by Sophia. They make a pleasant sound when you shake them, providing the beat for music and dance. She never thought she would be dancing at a ball. Controlling her body's movement was much more difficult than controlling machines. Still, she found herself enjoying it somehow.The one thing she remembers the most about that moment was the rhythm her partner made with the maracas. She no longer has a chance to dance lately. She wants to keep this wonderful instrument at your place for now while she looks forward to dancing with her partner and the shakers once again in the future.

Name: Warrior's Greatsword
Description: An item Kamui sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: A common weapon used in popular RPGs during the Golden Age. A replica like this has not been manufactured for a long time, so this is probably one of Kamui's prized processions. A line is engraved on the sword: "All in war with time". He has given you his sword, alongside his passion, courage, and faith unreservedly.

Name: Takeaway
Description: An item Camu sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: The standard lunchbox given out by Babylonia. After some modifications from Camu, the box looks distinctive and iconic, with its insulating alloy keeping the takeaway inside at the desired temperature. There are a few cheese hotteok in the first layer, and Camu's favorite nightmare-spicy golden egg fried rice is in the second. It does seem to be a dinner he originally prepared for himself. But if that was the case, why is the food not double-spicy the way Camu likes?

Name: Moon Rock
Description: An item Luna sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: An unpolished rock the size of a palm. Based on Luna's letter, this rock comes from the surface of the Moon. It was delivered among other packages for Babylonia, so it was thoroughly inspected, and no sign of the Punishing Virus was detected.Supposedly, some stones would glisten like the Moon in the past, earning them the name "moonstone." Meanwhile, this rock only glows ever so slightly, but its light is significantly warmer than the moonlight.Two Moons converged—and this is who she is now.

Name: Ticket To "Don Giovanni"
Description: An item Vera sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: An opera ticket sold by WGAA. The name of the opera and the showtime are printed on it. Despite WGAA's effort to update it for a modern audience, "Don Giovanni" still has a low turnout. The fact that this showing is taking place at 5:30 in the evening means there is barely any audience. Still, Vera will be waiting in that quiet, empty corner until the curtain falls.

Name: Camera
Description: An item Bianca sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: Bianca bought this vintage camera in the shopping town. Although the technology nowadays allows people to capture clearer images with cameras of much smaller sizes, but once can still discover a completely different world when they peek through this unit's viewfinder.

Name: A Container That Won't Forget
Description: An item Bambinata sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: The decoration on this small container was hand-crafted by Bambinata, inspired by the container that Vanessa customized for her. There is a brand-new notebook inside that she can write down the memorable moments. Bambinata once mentioned her "treasure box" that stored those things that were important to her at different times. Even if she has forgotten their origins when she sees them again, she never doubts their significance as long as they are in that box. Some memories last longer, while some are quickly forgotten. Bambinata gave you this container that she used to fight forgetfulness, in the hope that you can preserve as many important memories as possible.

Name: Masterpiece
Description: An item Ayla sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: This is the last work displayed in the art exhibition of Babylonia's renowned rising artist, Ayla. Only a blank canvas sits inside the beautiful and delicate frame, with a bouquet of peonies that she sent along. To finish this painting requires both of you, as she has already thought of the content: her muse. Once completed, it will be her magnum opus.

Name: "Whispers Of Valley Pines"
Description: An item Qu sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: Along with Qu's reply came an ancient scroll painting of Kowloong. Judging by the signature, this artwork is a millennium old. "In moss and dew, the dawn is bathed. Through veiled art, our souls are weighed. Upon the stones, pure waters rest. Through myriad valleys, pine winds wade." Anyone witnessing its beauty would surely be spellbound. It captures a moment in the Kowloong history, a serenity Qu will always aspire to but never quite reach.

Name: Beats & Beach Record: First Edition
Description: An item No. 21 sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: The CD's cover alone transports you back to the heights of summer passion. Long-forgotten beats and melodies surge to life at its mere sight. Rumor has it that this first edition CD was made exclusively for Beats & Beach attendees, with very limited quantities released to the public. Clearly played numerous times, it seems No. 21 has relived cherished memories with this time and again. Wait... there's a subtle scratch on the back. Could it be... teeth marks?

Name: Yesterday's Catch
Description: An item Rosetta sent along with the Activation Date mail.
WorldDesc: You sailed to the sea with Rosetta in the whispers of the waves under the starry night. When the day-breaking sun touched the gunwale, the ship was already filled with the gifts from the sea. When did she become such a skillful fisher? You figured out the answer spontaneously seeing the local residents waving at her on the shore.

Name: "The Fool"
Description: An item Nanami sent along with her mail.
WorldDesc: A tarot card created by an AI, combining the image of Nanami and "The Fool". To ensure her path will lead to "The World" she wants to see, Nanami is about to begin a long journey.

Name: "Church Visit"
Description: An item Haicma sent along with her mail.
WorldDesc: Plays the music video for "Church Visit". Featuring Haicma's synthesized voice, it introduces Church of Machina through a blend of rap, rock, folk, and pop music. Watching it leaves one in a trance for half an hour.

Name: Border Certificate
Description: The certificate of elite Commandant issued by Niflheim Lab. Get more of it to increase its quality and score.
WorldDesc: When facing unknown situation in "Virtual Horizon", all elite Commandants should be able to utilize all available team members and resources to complete their missions. The abilities of Commandant are demonstrated in the quality and score of this certificate. The ARU once believed that they would break through the arctic borders and become a formidable military force worldwide.

Name: Processing Unit
Description: Gestalt's processing unit. Collect more to increase its quality and score.
WorldDesc: Even a single processing unit of Gestalt also processes incredible computing power. As Gestalt is gradually repaired, the processing units available for teams to use will also level up.

Name: False Words Certificate
Description: Only issued to elite commandants who are authorized to view "False Words". Collect more to increase its quality and score.
WorldDesc: Only issued to elite commandants who are authorized to view "False Words". This certificate records the related data in "KI.GAL Archives".

Name: Honor Medal
Description: A medal issued by Babylonia to all the commandants who fought hard over the past year.
WorldDesc: The digital panel records the commandant's glorious achievements, and is decorated by a frame made from precious metal.

Name: Heterosoil Grown Certificate
Description: Only issued to elite commandants who are authorized to view "Heterosoil Grown". Collect more to increase its quality and score.
WorldDesc: Only issued to elite commandants who are authorized to view "Heterosoil Grown". This certificate records the related data in "KI.GAL Archives".

Description: An album full of precious memories with everyone. Hope these memories can fill your days in the future.

Name: Birthday Cake
Description: A birthday cake made by everyone. It is sprinkled with everyone's gratitude and blessings for Commandant.

Name: Birthday Bouquet
WorldDesc: Each member has picked a flower and made them into this birthday bouquet together. Each flower carries their unique gratitude and memories with Commandant.

Name: Birthday Card
WorldDesc: A birthday card created together by everyone and bearing all our blessings. Commandant, Happy Birthday!

Name: Birthday Mystery Box
WorldDesc: A surprise prepared by everyone together. This box is filled with precious bonds forged through time. Each gift within exists because of you and comes especially for you.

WorldDesc: Constructs and humans need to accumulate experiences over time, but Combat Unit Boosters just need to load the data — this naive belief only lasted until the first batch of Combat Unit Boosters was deployed in battle.

WorldDesc: An integrated data set with lots of combat experiences collected from Constructs and Combat Unit Boosters. It can quickly teach the Combat Unit Booster how to adapt to the battlefield and assist other combatants.

Name: Uniframe Crystal: Pavo
Description: Used as a material in [Pavo's] power modification.
WorldDesc: A crystal component that records massive battle data and greatly improves a Uniframe's battle performance.

Name: Uniframe Crystal: Tempest
Description: Used as a material in [Tempest's] power modification.
WorldDesc: A crystal component that records massive battle data and greatly improves a Uniframe's battle performance.

Name: Harmony Accelerator
WorldDesc: Developed by Science Council Section 2, this item can be used to upgrade a weapon's Harmony Level.

Name: Minor Overclock Alloy
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a small amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to enhance equipment of Constructs.

Name: Minor Overclock Alloy II
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a small amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to enhance equipment of Constructs.

Name: Minor Overclock Alloy III
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a small amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to enhance equipment of Constructs.

Name: Weapon Overclock Core I
Description: Key material used to increase weapon level limit. Useful for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Basic computing core that increases weapon strength.

Name: Memory Overclock Circuit I
Description: Key material used to increase Memory level limit. Useful for low-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Basic parts used to expand Memory Chip computing pathways and increase Memory strength.

Name: Major Overclock Alloy
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a large amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to increase the strength of Construct equipment.

Name: Major Overclock Alloy II
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a large amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to increase the strength of Construct equipment.

Name: Major Overclock Alloy III
Description: Used to exceed equipment level limit for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Parts containing a large amount of high-entropy alloy. Used to increase the strength of Construct equipment.

Name: Weapon Overclock Core II
Description: Key material used to increase weapon level limit. Useful for high-rank equipment.
WorldDesc: Advanced computing core that increases weapon strength.

Name: Memory Overclock Circuit II
Description: Key material used to increase weapon level limit. Useful for high-rank Memory.
WorldDesc: Advanced parts used to expand Memory Chip computing pathways and increase Memory strength.

Name: Support Overclock Bundle (S)
Description: A modification bundle prepared for Combat Unit Boosters. It can remove the level limit on low-rank Combat Unit Boosters.
WorldDesc: To evolve to the next stage, creatures need to go through substantial hard work and suffering. This also applies to Combat Unit Boosters.

Name: Support Overclock Bundle (L)
Description: A modification bundle prepared for Combat Unit Boosters. It can remove the level limit on high-rank Combat Unit Boosters.
WorldDesc: The special tool and material bundle required for further modification of Combat Unit Boosters after they have accumulated sufficient experience.

Name: Support Skill Component
Description: With Combat Unit Booster's skill data loaded, this can increase the skill level of Combat Unit Boosters.
WorldDesc: The combat data of Constructs and Combat Unit Boosters is refined and analyzed. By learning such data, the skill module of Combat Unit Boosters can be further optimized.

Name: Frog Accessory
Description: Increases member's Affection. Lucia's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A series of plushies produced by a famous toy-maker brand. Poor sales meant that there are very few of them left.

Name: Biosphere
Description: Increases member's Affection. Liv's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Highly advanced device that holds a self-contained ecosystem, a popular science teaching tool in Babylonia.

Name: Precision Toolkit
Description: Increases member's Affection. Lee's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Toolkit used for the maintenance of electronics.

Name: Jack-in-the-box
Description: Increases member's Affection. Nanami's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Trick box that surprises those who touch it.

Name: Prototype Engine
Description: Increases member's Affection. Karenina's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Simple and powerful, but with a tendency to explode when overloaded - which some people do not see as a flaw.

Name: Portable Game Console
Description: Increases member's Affection. Kamui's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: The newest portable game console, perfect for passing the time between missions. Who is behind the anonymous account at the top of the rankings?

Name: MRE Rations
Description: Increases member's Affection. Watanabe's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Popular ration set that contains a main dish, a side course, and coffee. You may even get rare seasoning such as miso if you are lucky.

Name: Lily Brooch
Description: Increases member's Affection. Bianca's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: The lily represents selflessness and dignity.

Name: Painting Kit
Description: Increases member's Affection. Ayla's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A painting kit released by the most popular art supply brand "Montpellier", which is dedicated to sharing the happiness of artistic creation to everyone. Montpellier is always an artist's choice.

Name: High-Power Batteries
Description: Increases member's Affection. Sophia's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Batteries for power tools. No mechanics want to find themselves out of batteries during work, right?

Name: R3 Cleaning Robot
Description: Increases member's Affection. Chrome's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Developed by Cosmos Industries for Babylonia's domestic market, this cleaning robot is the best solution to a nice and clean environment.

Name: Military-Grade Bionic Dog
Description: Increases member's Affection. Vera's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A small military-grade bionic dog that performs various functions from item storage to radar detection, with its absolute loyalty to its master being its biggest selling point. It's been widely acclaimed ever since it was released by General Toys.

Name: Media Player
Description: Increases member's Affection. Camu's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A peripheral media player device attached to a Construct. Can receive messages and signals from Babylonia.

Name: Weather Glass
Description: Increases member's Affection. Rosetta's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Looking inside this glass bottle can remind you of those snowy nights.

Name: Antique Book
Description: Increases member's Affection. Qu's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: This paper-made book is a rare sight when the majority of information is stored digitally. Take extra caution when reading it, for both the content and the book itself are of high value.

Name: Copper Coin
Description: Increases member's Affection. Changyu's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Issued by KCC in the Golden Age, this commemorative coin provides a peek into the KCC's prime days. The pattern on it is still clearly visible.

Name: Night Light
Description: Increases member's Affection. Luna's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A small light may dispel darkness from the night. It reminded Luna of those scary nights without her sister or light.

Name: Lunar Tear
Description: Increases member's Affection. 2B, 9S and A2's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A decoration made from rare flowers. It seems to glow under the moonlight.

Name: Hugging Pillow
Description: Increases member's Affection. Wanshi's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: One can find lots of these pillows in Strike Hawk's recovery room. It's soft, simple, and can bring sweet dreams to those using it.

Name: Iris
Description: Increases member's Affection. Selena's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Babylonia seldom wastes resources on ornamental flowers. If you can bring an iris from the surface, put it behind her ear, and you will see a smile more beautiful than the flower.

Name: Audiovisual Terminal
Description: Increases member's Affection. No. 21's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: An audio-visual terminal that repeatedly plays various videos, including some programs revived from the golden age. No. 21 seems to be addicted to watching the terminal in her spare time, learning all kinds of content displayed.

Name: Marionette
Description: Increases member's Affection. Roland's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A hand-made puppet that can be moved by a controller. When Roland was an actor, he often used different marionettes to make plays, giving them different identities such as kings, servants, or family. Now he seems to have found someone to walk along in his lone journey.

Name: Panda Change Purse
Description: Increases member's Affection. Pulao's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A cute panda change purse. Pulao used to imagine how it looks like when it's full of Grubs, but unfortunately, it is empty most of the time...

Name: Deluxe Picture Book
Description: Increases member's Affection. Haicma's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A paper picture book published by WGAA with masterpieces of various themes. Haicma loves the diversity of the book, especially the blank page left at the end for the reader to create their own work. Haicma plans to complete it with someone in the future.

Name: Notebook and Pen
Description: Increases member's Affection. Noan's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: An ordinary notebook and pen. Noan writes and draws with them.

Name: Music Box
Description: Increases member's Affection. Bambinata's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: An exquisite ceramic music box. Once wound up, the music starts and the ballerina comes alive. As long as the music goes on, so too will the ballerina. This is a fragile item. Please handle it with care.

Name: Cloud Comb
Description: Increases member's Affection. Hanying's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: "The clouds are untroubled, the waters edgeless. The sound of a flute locks emptiness into the room. When can these two drift as one with the spring moon, in a boat between steep banks of drooping willows? Kowloong ladies seem to like this simple yet elegant wooden comb. When given as a gift, it is a symbol of longing."

Name: Ironclad Boxing Gloves
Description: Increases member's Affection. Noctis' favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Made from a special macromolecule material, these boxing gloves are a must-have for the most hardcore boxing fans. The instruction manual states: Rest assured that they can stay with you through a lifetime (we recommend changing them every 3 months for Constructs).

Name: Gavel
Description: Increases member's Affection. Alisa's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Made by the shopping street, this small gift mimics the gavel used in a courtroom. It is a symbol of judgment, laws, and unbiased justice.

Name: Coffee Cup
Description: Increases member's Affection. Lamia's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Ordinary coffee cups, which Lamia has been occasionally seen stacking together with a wistful expression to pass the time.

Name: Star Accessory
Description: Increases member's Affection. BLACK★ROCK SHOOTER's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A small accessory with a star. It seems to be quite popular among young women.

Name: Teddy
Description: Increases member's Affection. Teddy's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A once-popular brand of teddy bear that can be customized any way you want. Christina had one when she was very young, but it was thrown away for some reason. Will she like this new teddy bear you customized for her?

Name: Tactical Sunglasses
Description: Increases member's Affection. Bridget's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: These sunglasses look similar to regular fashion eyewear but are actually a multi-purpose combat device crafted with UV-resistant lenses. It is said that they have adopted a vintage Golden Age design to suit the user's personal preference.

Name: Hydrangea Bouquet
Description: Increases member's Affection. Yata's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: The soft, pale petals remind her of a carefree summer sky, carrying the girl's thoughts back to that endless summer.

Name: Copperwood Dice
Description: Increases member's Affection. Ishmael's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A twenty-sided dice used in tabletop games to decide the success or failure of each attempt. Yet, while a dice brings in variables, they will never stray beyond the game's script. So, are these outcomes truly coincidental, or are they inevitable?

Name: Cardistry Poker
Description: Increases member's Affection. Lilith's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A poker set commonly seen in Las Prados. Made with collection-level techniques, the cards feel smooth during shuffling and cutting. They work wonders in Lilith's hands.

Name: "White Box"
Description: Increases member's Affection. Jetavie's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: A virtual reality hard drive shaped like a Rubik's Cube. Its internal data has been rigorously sanitized, making it a safe choice for "feeding" to AI models. Its rich, vibrant world data makes it extremely popular among mechanoids and mechanical consciousnesses. It is also equipped with a human consciousness interface for developers to debug... or even play with AI together.

Name: Poetry Collection
Description: Increases member's Affection. Vergil's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Even Vergil himself can't tell when he started to love reading poetry collections.

Name: Pizza Combo
Description: Increases member's Affection. Dante's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: "There's only one thing that I can't stand and that is the olives on the pizza!" —Dante

Name: Scissors
Description: Increases member's Affection. Discord's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: Discord's favorite sewing tools.

Name: Weapon Charm
Description: Increases member's Affection. Veronica's favorite gift.
WorldDesc: An elegant charm crafted from durable metal, perfect for decorating weapons.

Name: Best-Seller
Description: Increases members' Affection. A common gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Serialized manga that has been a best-seller both on a ground and in Babylonia since the last century, depicting the human struggle against the Punishing Virus.

Name: Vinyl Record
Description: Increases members' Affection. A common gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Specialized teams have been sent to earth to retrieve the sounds, sights and culture that could not be artificially recreated, resulting in this record of a golden era long gone.

Name: Ration Chocolate
Description: Increases members' Affection. An exquisite gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: Chocolate bar used as rations by the United Earth military. Has a very long shelf life with a wide variety of flavors. A delicious gift.

Name: 1 Day Tour Tickets x2
Description: Increases members' Affection. An exquisite gift everybody likes.
WorldDesc: A pair of bracelet tickets for 2 people to enjoy a day tour of Babylonia, including transport, space observation deck tickets, VIP hologram theater seats, as well as bar and outdoor pool party access.

Name: Normal Gift Box
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Fine Gift Box
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Precious Gift Box
WorldDesc: A wrapped gift box. No way to know what is inside without opening it.

Name: Sweet Gift Box
Description: Choose 1 from 3 gifts: Precision Toolkit, Portable Game Console, MRE Rations.
WorldDesc: A gift box wrapped with a ribbon. It contains male members' favorite gifts.

Name: Beating Heart Gift
Description: Choose 1 from 6 gifts: Frog Accessory, Biosphere, Jack-in-the-box, Prototype Engine, Lily Brooch, Painting Kit.
WorldDesc: An exquisite gift box that contains female members' favorite gifts.

Name: Crimson Love
Description: Members give this rare collectible to their Commandant on May 20th. It carries special meanings.
WorldDesc: Members have prepared this rose for a special day. It's been carefully sealed within a box so it can be preserved permanently.

Name: White Affection
Description: All members love this rare gift. Give it to them on a special day to create some great memories.
WorldDesc: A customized rose for your important ones. Costs a lot to make, and contains a lot of emotions.

Name: Voice of Thoughts
Description: Gifts given by members to the commandant on White Day express their strong affection.
WorldDesc: Audiovisual product specifically tailored for commandants. Carefully sealed in a collection box, only special people can open it.

Name: Radiant Comradery
Description: A gift given to members on a special day to express affection and leave a beautiful lasting memory.
WorldDesc: A retro machine that can play audio and video stored on a specific medium. Beneath the elegant shell lies a sincere heart.

Name: Eternal Bond
Description: An important collectible given by a member to the commandant. It carries the sender's intense, ever-lasting affection.
WorldDesc: This special gift has been meticulously customized and prepared for someone important. Only the special person can open it.

Name: Affectionate Melody
Description: A gift given to a member on a special day to express your heartfelt emotions, engraved with beautiful memories and aspirations for the future.
WorldDesc: This hand crank music box is a rare sight nowadays. All the affections are hidden between the notes on the music sheet made by you.

Name: Whispers of Love
Description: An important collectible given by a member to the commandant on White Day, March 14. It carries the sender's intense, genuine affection.
WorldDesc: Special feelings, important thoughts, everything the giver wants to say is inside the box, waiting for that special someone.

Name: Fragrant Whispers
Description: A gift given to a member on a special day to express your heartfelt emotions, engraved with beautiful memories and aspirations for the future.
WorldDesc: Handmade cookies of specially selected shapes. The aroma holds the genuine feelings and affection of the giver.

Name: Heartwarming Moment
Description: An important collectible given by a member to the commandant on Double Seventh Festival. It carries the sender's intense, genuine affection.
WorldDesc: Travel beyond time and space just to meet with the special one.

Name: Heartfelt Letter
Description: A gift given to a member on a special day to express your heartfelt emotions, engraved with beautiful memories and aspirations for the future.
WorldDesc: A handpicked commemorative travel postcard that records the beautiful sceneries and precious handwritten heartfelt words with a special Double Seventh Festival postmark.

Name: Reagent He-4
Description: Fusion reagent dropped from deep ocean Corrupted. Can be exchanged for items in Frozen Darkness.
WorldDesc: Deep ocean Corrupted store He-4 generated by their internal fusion reactors in special containers, which are considered valuable resources.

Name: Overclock Material Box (α)
Description: Gives a random low-grade overclock material.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Overclock Material Box (β)
Description: Gives a random high-grade overclock material.
WorldDesc: Contains data of an unknown nature. Open it to decipher its secrets.

Name: Christmas Decor Blueprint Set
WorldDesc: A fine Christmas gift box. No way to know which blueprint is inside without opening it.

Name: Heteromer Sample
Description: A sample of Hetero-matter produced by Hetero-Core that can be used in exchange for supplies in Aerial Supply.
WorldDesc: Hetero-derivatives are produced by the Punishing Virus under special environmental conditions. Dense and solid in texture, its behaviors are far more complicated than that of Punishing Virus.

Name: Space Station Battlelog
Description: A battlelog from the space station that can be used in exchange for Battlelog Reward.
WorldDesc: This battlelog not only records and summarizes the combats that occurred every day but also helps you figure out how to enrich Construct's combat experience and skills... Someone said and took out a precious Space Station Battlelog Collector's Edition.

Name: Heteromer Crystal
Description: Raw material for Heteromer Layer Experiment. Conduct Heteromer Layer Experiment to get the Research supplies from Babylonia.
WorldDesc: The pure nucleus formed because of the large structure fluctuation of liquid Hetero-matter. The top-tier scientists of Babylonia are dedicated to the study of Hetero-Core through Heteromer Crystal.

Name: Akdilek Coin
Description: Currency issued by Akdilek that can be used in exchange for items in the event shop.
WorldDesc: With a high level of trading proficiency, Akdilek Commercial Alliance has turned Akdilek Coin into a currency that is even more valuable than rare metals in various regions. Now it is one of the most popular currencies for trading.

Name: Magnetic Ticket
Description: Eternal Throne Abyss Pass (returns 6★ Memory Shard x10 when expired)
WorldDesc: A brand new first-class magnetic ticket with an Akdilek logo and station number. It can be used to enter certain special regions.

Name: Royal Token
Description: A royal token from Asslam that is given as a reward for outstanding merit. Can be used in exchange for corresponding rewards.
WorldDesc: If one can earn respect and trust from the aristocrats on the train, this rare token will be offered as the highest honor given by them.

Name: Support Point
Description: Support permit issued by Babylonia. Can be used to apply for different supports from Babylonia during the mission.
WorldDesc: To support commandants' operation, Babylonia provides support points that can be used to request different supports from Babylonia without President's authorization.

Name: Halloween Candy
Description: Halloween candies provided by Babylonia. Give them to good kids.
WorldDesc: Use it to increase the power of Pet: Michael in Book of Toro.

Name: Toro Coupon
Description: This Babylonia-issued voucher has Commandant's image printed on it. Use it to ask Babylonia for advanced support during your mission.
WorldDesc: Babylonia issued this certificate in order to assist the operations of commandants. It can provide better than usual support when used.

Name: Metal Grub
Description: A currency circulating around the Nighter. Can be used in the Virtual Mart.
WorldDesc: Even when separated, the offspring of the mythological water-beetle qingfu will always return to their mother. Issued by the KCC, the qingfu coin is a symbol of accumulating wealth. Also called grub by the locals.

Name: Holographic Ticket
Description: Cornered in Cruise - Abyss Pass (returns 6★ Memory Shard x10 when expired)
WorldDesc: The first class ticket issued by Kowloong Chamber of Commerce. Use it to watch a holographic puppet show of the performance troupe up close.

Name: Electronic Stamp
Description: Issued by the financial department of KCC, this Electronic Stamp has "Qu" printed on it and can be exchanged for items via the terminals.
WorldDesc: The Electronic Stamps backed by the leader of KCC, "Qu", are proofs of transactions on the Nighter. It serves as both an ID and a trade credit across all the financial terminals.

Name: Titanium Token
Description: Forged from titanium extracted from scrapped mechanical parts, this token is chosen as a widely circulating currency in the microchip market for its lightness and corrosion resistance.
WorldDesc: A new alloy currency issued under the authorization of Asimov, this token is only available in the Memory Chip market. It also works as an ID and a certificate of the Memory Chip knowledge, and is necessary for the purchase of any high-spec components.

Name: Crystal Note
Description: A currency circulating in Kowloong Metropolis. Can be exchanged for items in Kowloong Market.
WorldDesc: An easy-to-carry, ultra slim transaction card issued by Bank of Kowloong. Made from semi-transparent micro crystals, this card has a micro-photon chip inside. A complicated circuit-like glowing pattern is printed on its surface. —"Bank of Kowloong specializes in everything."

Name: Dragon Jade
Description: Dragon Jades are only produced in Kowlong City. They can be exchanged for items in Rosary Path.
WorldDesc: A glossy jade pendant with a vivid floating dragon carved on it. Rumor has it that some mysterious merchants would offer a fortune for this luxurious token...

Name: Morning Star Cup
Description: Randomly dropped in event stages that have a Serum cost. Can be exchanged for Sorbet Summer event mission rewards.
WorldDesc: The Venus Splash Park limited edition ice-cream cup. Ticket holders can get a free cup from A'Mao. Made from strawberries, chocolate flakes, cream, and a paper card of Shark-speare. Note: The paper is not edible.

Name: Square Chip
Description: Can be used to flip one tile in Summer Flip.
WorldDesc: An exquisite square chip, used as a token for the wildly popular board game in the central arcade in Venus Splash Park. Win a certain amount of them and you get to take home all the prizes sealed away in the glass cabinet. Want to try your luck?

Name: One-Point Dice
Description: Can be used in Summer Flip. Allows you to select a reward icon and move it one tile.
WorldDesc: A beautifully crafted six-sided dice, used in the board game in the central arcade of Venus Splash Park. All its six sides bear the same number: "1"—so no matter how you throw it, you will always wind up moving one step.

Name: Heat Mixture
Description: A currency circulating around the Arctic Route Union. Can be used in the Snow Depot.
WorldDesc: Issued by the Arctic Route Union. One of the common supplies that humans living in the arctic region rely on. Quickly heats up upon use.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 1
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Name: Summer Snapshots Puzzle Piece 2
Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.

Description: A puzzle piece used in Summer Snapshots.
WorldDesc: A puzzle piece used to activate the corresponding puzzle in Summer Snapshots.
